was too damn busy. Did, how did you feel about? Oh, 
yeah, we had another one. We had Langford, not the

29:17.251 --> 29:32.027
one you know, but they had a man called Langford 
that he was working on

29:17.251 --> 29:32.027
freight race. That was in there. That was mixed up 
in there. So I had a, you know, I didn't like that.

29:39.989 --> 29:57.671
And across the street, across the, that was on the 
east side of the, in the fourth floor up there, and

29:39.989 --> 29:57.671
on the other side there was, was Dr. Lindsey, who 
was head of the, came from the Lindsey and Ingram

29:39.989 --> 29:57.671
department. And he had three boys,

29:57.691 --> 30:08.545
one of them a doctor, one of them would take care of 
your life, your eye case, and one of them a lawyer. I

30:08.930 --> 30:10.932
knew all three of them. I knew the old man too. Who 
was the A&M president when you got back?

30:20.965 --> 30:22.807
I don't know. Gilchrist? I guess Gilchrist was. 
